Marc H Bell's Experience
Title: Chief Executive Officer
               Company: 123jump.com Inc
Job Details
               The Company has been providing pet supplies and products for over 35 years. The Company's products include pet food, supplies, grooming products, toys, novelty items and vitamins, small pets such as fish, birds and other small animals (excluding cats and dogs), and veterinary supplies. The Company's strategy is to offer its customers a complete assortment of pet-related products at competitive prices, with superior levels of customer service at convenient locations. Although services do not represent a significant portion of the Company's net sales, it believes that offering selected pet services better serves the best customers and increases traffic flow in the Company's stores. The Company also offers obedience training in most of its stores, grooming in many of its stores and limited veterinary services, such as routine vaccinations, at a number of stores.  The Company's stores combine the broad merchandise selection and everyday low prices of a pet supply warehouse store with the convenient location and knowledgeable customer service of a neighborhood pet supply store. The Company believes that this combination differentiates its stores and provides it with a competitive advantage. The Company's principal format is a 15,000 square foot superstore, conveniently located near local neighborhood shopping destinations, including supermarkets, bookstores, coffee shops, dry cleaners and video stores, where the Company's target "pet parent" customer makes regular weekly shopping trips. The Company believes that its stores are well positioned, both in terms of product offerings and location, to benefit from favorable long-term demographic trends, a growing pet population and an increasing willingness of pet owners to spend on their pets.  The Company's centralized purchasing and distribution system minimizes the delivered cost of merchandise and maximizes the in-stock position of its stores. The Company currently operates three central and five regional distribution centers. The central distribution centers are located in Mira Loma, California; Dayton, New Jersey; and Joliet, Illinois. Bulk items for all stores are either shipped to regional distribution centers for redistribution or are sent directly to store locations. Manufacturers ship non-bulk supplies to the central distribution facilities which are then distribute either to regional centers or directly to store locations. The Company believes that its centralized distribution system enables its stores to maximize selling space by reducing necessary levels of safety stock carried in each store. The Company also provides order fulfillment services for its Internet customers through its three central distribution centers.
