OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Marc H. Bell  Chief Executive Officer and Director, FastCupid, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 24 Board Members in 24 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships50--
Background

		Mr. Marc H. Bell is Founder of NAFT International Ltd. Mr. Bell was the Founder at NEON Communications Group, Inc. and served as its Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, from 1989 to August 1, 2001. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Various, Inc. Mr. Bell serves as the Managing Director at Marc Bell Capital Partners LLC. He founded the Marc Bell Capital Partners in 2003. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Penthouse Media Group Inc. since ... October 2004. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer at Penthouse Magazine. He has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Blue Hen Group Inc. since October 17, 2011. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President of General Media Communications, Inc., General Media Art Holding, Inc., GMCI Internet Operations, Inc.,Global Alphabet, Inc., Penthouse Images Acquisitions, Ltd., GMI On-Line Ventures, Ltd., Giant Swallowtail Inc., PPM Technology Group, Inc., Magnolia Blossom Inc., General Media Entertainment, Inc., Goldenrod Spear Inc., and Friendfinder Ventures Inc. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Big Island Technology Group, Inc., Pure Entertainment Telecommunications, Inc., Medley.Com Inc., West Coast Facilities Inc. and Fastcupid, Inc. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Interactive Network Inc. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Traffic Cat, Inc., Sharkfish, Inc. and Friendfinder California, Inc. He served as Chief Executive Officer at Friendfinder Networks Inc. from October 2004 to July 2012 and also served as its Chief Strategy Officer and Executive Co-Chairman of The Board from July 2012 to October 5, 2012. He served as the President of Friendfinder Networks Inc. since October 2004. He founded Globix Corporation and served as its President. He served as Principal Financial Officer and Principal Accounting Officer of Enterprise Acquisition Corp. until January 10, 2008. He served as Treasurer and Chairman of Enterprise Acquisition Corp. since July 09, 2007. Mr. Bell founded numerous companies in his career and has been a seed investor in several start-up entities including iFilm, Vault.com, NetSat Express, Edgar Online, Earnings.com and SpamEx. Previously, he served as the Chairman of Globix Corporation, from 1998 to 2003, Chief Executive Officer, from 1998 to 2001 and also served as its President. Mr. Bell serves as the Chairman of the Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences at New York University. He served as Non Executive Co-Chairman of The Board at Friendfinder Networks Inc. since October 5, 2012. He served as Chairman of NEON Communications Group, Inc. since August 01, 2001 and also served as its Director. He serves as a Director of Pure Entertainment Telecommunications, Inc. Mr. Bell has been a Director of Penthouse Media Group, Inc since October 2004. He has been a Director of Friendfinder Networks Inc. since October 2004 and Blue Hen Group Inc. since October 17, 2011. He has been a Director of ARMOUR Residential REIT, Inc. since November 06, 2009. He serves as a Director of Various, Inc., PPM Technology Group, Inc., Traffic Cat, Inc., Interactive Network Inc., Friendfinder California, Inc., Sharkfish, Inc., General Media Art Holding, Inc., GMCI Internet Operations, Inc., Global Alphabet, Inc., Penthouse Images Acquisitions, Ltd., General Media Communications, Inc., GMI On-Line Ventures, Ltd., XVHUB Group Inc., Magnolia Blossom Inc., Big Island Technology Group, Inc., Medley.Com Inc., General Media Entertainment, Inc., Goldenrod Spear Inc., West Coast Facilities Inc., Friendfinder Ventures Inc. and Fastcupid, Inc. He served as a Director of JAVELIN Mortgage Investment Corp. from June 18, 2012 to 2016. He served as a Director of EDGAR Online Inc., from 1998 to 2000. Mr. Bell has been a director of ARMOUR since November 2009 and was the Chairman of the Board of Directors and Treasurer of Enterprise from its inception in 2007 until its merger with ARMOUR in November 2009. He serves as a Member of the Board of Trustees of New York University, New York University School of Medicine and Babson College. Mr. Bell serves as a Trustee at the Citizens Budget Commission. He is an Adjunct professor at the Global Entrepreneurship Center of Florida International University, where he taught graduate courses in Entrepreneurship. Mr. Bell has appeared on numerous television broadcasts and has been quoted in several national publications regarding Internet-related topics. He is a co-producer of several Broadway musicals and plays like Jersey Boys, The Wedding Singer, August: Osage County and A Catered Affair. Mr. Bell founded Marc and Ruti Bell Foundation in 2001 to foster education and medical research. He has been a winner of the American Theatre Wing's Tony Award ‘2008 Best Play’ for August: Osage County and ‘2006 Best Musical’ for Jersey Boys. Mr. Bell holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Accounting from Babson College and an M.S. degree in Real Estate Development, investment and finance from New York University.Read Full Background




